    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>July 16<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>Through reflexion &amp; by reading what little has been written on subject, I do not doubt but that you will find interesting points to observe.—<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I can think of only one point, &amp; the possibility of attending to this will depend on your possessing an accurate musical ear, namely the various intonations, which young children utter, before they can speak, &amp; just after they have learned to do so.— Many of their sounds in different notes are highly expressive.</p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
